</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2A7836CB196429477486F9C2FD36F97C" blockId="52.[212,1172,1501,1691]" pageId="52" pageNumber="627">
The female differs from that of 
<taxonomicName id="EDC74D4819642947766FF9C4FD21F9FB" authority="Santos &amp; Melo, 2014" authorityName="Santos &amp; Melo" authorityYear="2014" box="[573,739,1540,1564]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Megalopta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="52" pageNumber="627" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="munduruku" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="18B3EAD919642947766FF9C4FD21F9FB" box="[573,739,1540,1564]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="627">M. munduruku</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="038057A21964294776B9F9C5FCEBF9FC" box="[747,809,1540,1563]" pageId="52" pageNumber="627" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
by mid depression extending to posterior margin in basal area of metapostnotum (
<figureCitation id="B2FC2A4E19642947775DF9E2FC46F9DC" box="[783,900,1571,1595]" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="9.[144,211,1402,1424]" captionTargetBox="[144,1104,168,1365]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[144,1104,168,1370]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figure 4. Females of Megalopta. (A‒E) Posterolateral view of mesosoma; (A) Megalopta yanomami sp. n. from Parauapebas, Brazil; (B) M. piraha sp. n. from Manaus, Brazil; (C) M. munduruku sp. n. from Belterra, Brazil; (D) M. cuprea Friese from Nigrillani, Bolivia; (E) M. sodalis Vachal from Antonina, Brazil; (F) frontal view of head of M. xavante sp. n from Nova Xavantina, Brazil. Scale bar 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4004467" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4004467/files/figure.png" pageId="52" pageNumber="627">Figure 4D</figureCitation>
) and the male, by basal area of metapostnotum with longer and strongly impressed longitudinal rugulosities (
<figureCitation id="B2FC2A4E19642947748EF9A2FE9DF99C" box="[220,351,1635,1659]" captionStart="Figure 13" captionStartId="21.[144,211,1401,1423]" captionTargetBox="[144,1104,168,1369]" captionTargetId="figure@21.[144,1104,168,1369]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="Figure 13. Males of Megalopta. (A, B) Posterolateral view of mesosoma; (C, E) frontal view of head; (D) frontal view of flagellomeres; (A) M. cuprea Friese from Santa Cruz, Bolivia; (B) M. sodalis Vachal from Antonina, Brazil; (C, D) M. yanomami sp. n. from Parauapebas, Brazil; (E) M. piraha sp. n. from Manaus, Brazil; (F) M. cuprea Friese from Espejo, Santa Cruz, Bolivia. Scale bar 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4004485" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4004485/files/figure.png" pageId="52" pageNumber="627">Figure 13A</figureCitation>
); both sexes can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="EDC74D4819642947777DF9A5FC67F99B" box="[815,933,1636,1660]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Megalopta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="52" pageNumber="627" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sodalis">
<emphasis id="18B3EAD919642947777DF9A5FC67F99B" box="[815,933,1636,1660]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="627">M. sodalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by head and thorax mostly dark brown, lacking metallic reflections.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
